Parameters.Name: Fueling Mode
Parameters.ToolTipText: Choose whether to run the engine in batch mode, grouped or fully sequential. Grouped fires the injectors in two groups, 360* apart. First group will be odd-numbered injectors, then, after 360*, the even-numbered ones. Fully sequential depends on the firing order selected in the engine driver.

Parameters.Name: Use IAT in Algorithm
Parameters.ToolTipText: WARNING: Leave this to 'yes' unless told to change it.

Parameters.Name: Default IAT
Parameters.ToolTipText: Default IAT value to be used by fuelling algorithm.

Parameters.Name: Injection Angle Specifier
Parameters.ToolTipText: Select whether the injection angle specifies the beginning of the injection pulse or its end.

Parameters.Name: Inj Max Duty (%)
Parameters.ToolTipText: The maximum duty allowed for injectors.

Parameters.Name: Pri. Inj Size (cc/min)
Parameters.ToolTipText: The flow-rate of your primary fuel injectors (individually) at the reference pressure - in cc/min

Parameters.Name: Fuel Pressure
Parameters.ToolTipText: The fuel pressure your fuel rail runs at. This then computes the true fuel flow in cc/min through each injector.

Parameters.Name: Inj Ref. Pressure
Parameters.ToolTipText: The pressure at which your injectors flow the above quoted cc/min. This is usually 300-350KPa.

Parameters.Name: Fuel Pump Prime Time (s)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Fuel pump priming pulse duration in seconds.

Parameters.Name: Prime on Key On
Parameters.ToolTipText: With this set to YES, there will be a priming pulse on key-on.

Parameters.Name: Prime on Cranking
Parameters.ToolTipText: With this set to YES, there will be a priming pulse every time the engine starts.

Parameters.Name: Staged Injection
Parameters.ToolTipText: WARNING: Leave this to 'Disabled' unless told to change it by a member of our staff.

Parameters.Name: Sec. Inj Size (cc/min)
Parameters.ToolTipText: The flow-rate of your secondary fuel injectors - in cc/min

Parameters.Name: Min Sec Inj PW (ms)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Min PW (in addition to the defined injector dead time) required for the secondary injectors to start operating.

Parameters.Name: Cranking Min. RPM
Parameters.ToolTipText: The minimum RPM at which we consider the engine cranking. Typically 50rpm.

Parameters.Name: Cranking Max. RPM
Parameters.ToolTipText: The MAXIMUM RPM at which we consider the engine cranking. Typically 300rpm.

Parameters.Name: Acc. Source
Parameters.ToolTipText: The source of acceleration delta, or rate of change. If you have a throttle sensor, then TPS is prefered, otherwise you can use the MAP sensor.

Parameters.Name: Hold Rotations
Parameters.ToolTipText: After AE is triggered, the amount of revolutions of the engine the extra fuel is added.

Parameters.Name: Decay Rotations
Parameters.ToolTipText: After AE is triggered, and the Hold Rotations have elapsed, this is the amount of revolutions of the engine the extra fuel is decayed to zero over.

Parameters.Name: Deadband(%/s)
Parameters.ToolTipText: The mimum AE Delta that needs to occurs before AE is triggered. Typically 10-20 bigger than the maximum delta recorded under steady state driving.

Parameters.Name: Mode
Parameters.ToolTipText: Type of limiter cut to be employed.

Parameters.Name: Soft Cut RPM Offset
Parameters.ToolTipText: This value defines when the event cutting being in relationship to the set RPM limit. The ignition/injection cutting gets more aggresive as the engine's RPM gets closer to the set limit.

Parameters.Name: On Fan
Parameters.ToolTipText: Selects which fan determines the idle duty adder to be applied.

Parameters.Name: Idle Duty Add.
Parameters.ToolTipText: PWM Duty to be added to already existing idle duty.

Parameters.Name: Idle Duty Add. Delay(s)
Parameters.ToolTipText: How much time, after applying the adder, should be elapse before turning on the selected fan.

Parameters.Name: On Temp. for Primary Fan
Parameters.ToolTipText: The coolant temperature in Degrees C that the main coolant Fan will turn on.

Parameters.Name: Off Temp. for Primary Fan
Parameters.ToolTipText: The coolant temperature in Degrees C that the main coolant Fan will turn off. Typically 3-4 degrees lower than the on temperature.

Parameters.Name: On Temp. for Secondary Fan
Parameters.ToolTipText: The coolant temperature in Degrees C that the secondary coolant Fan will turn on.

Parameters.Name: Off Temp. for Secondary Fan
Parameters.ToolTipText: The coolant temperature in Degrees C that the secondary coolant Fan will turn off. Typically 3-4 degrees lower than the on temperature.

Parameters.Name: Ref. Voltage
Parameters.ToolTipText: Analog Reference Voltage to scale raw readings from.

Parameters.Name: Mode
Parameters.ToolTipText: The idle control strategy. For test purposes, select Manual Duty and use the Manual Duty field in the driver to have direct control of the valve.

Parameters.Name: Drive
Parameters.ToolTipText: The idle drive mode.

Parameters.Name: Extra Load Add.(%)
Parameters.ToolTipText: How much to add to idle DC when the "extra load input" is active.

Parameters.Name: SW Active
Parameters.ToolTipText: Input value when switch is active.

Parameters.Name: PWM Base Freq.
Parameters.ToolTipText: The base frequency of the PWM Idle Solenoid. This varies dependant on the valve.

Parameters.Name: PWM Valve Control Pin
Parameters.ToolTipText: using 'Manual Mode' you can discover if more duty means more or less airflow. If more duty means more air flow, then set to normal, otherwise, set this to inverted. The displayed Duty is always the amount of airflow. More Duty means more airflow, even though the valve may be being driven invertdly due to this setting.

Parameters.Name: PWM Min Duty
Parameters.ToolTipText: The minimum 'effective' duty of the PWM Idle Solenoid. This varies dependant on the valve. Used for PID Closed loop control.

Parameters.Name: PWM Max Duty
Parameters.ToolTipText: The maximum 'effective' duty of the PWM Idle Solenoid. This varies dependant on the valve. Used for PID Closed loop control.

Parameters.Name: DBW TP Max
Parameters.ToolTipText: The maximum allowed throttle plate opening that can be requested by the idle algorithm.

Parameters.Name: Type
Parameters.ToolTipText: Type of stepper to be drive.

Parameters.Name: Number of Steps
Parameters.ToolTipText: The number of steps from min to max position.

Parameters.Name: Step Time(ms)
Parameters.ToolTipText: How many ms per step.

Parameters.Name: Direction
Parameters.ToolTipText: Set such that increasing the stepper position always increases airflow.

Parameters.Name: PWM Manual Duty
Parameters.ToolTipText: When Idle mode is set to Manual Duty, you can enter a duty here to drive the valve for test purposes, or leave it as a fixed idle setting.

Parameters.Name: CL Start Inc(%)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Adder to be used when starting, before switching to closed loop.

Parameters.Name: CL Start Delay(s)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Time, in seconds, for which the OL algorithm (plus adder) is used when starting, before switching to closed loop.

Parameters.Name: CL RTI Inc(%)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Adder to be used when returning to idle, before switching to closed loop.

Parameters.Name: CL RTI Delay(s)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Time, in seconds, for which the OL algorithm (plus adder) is used when returning to idle, before switching to closed loop.

Parameters.Name: OL Idle Inc(%)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Adder to be used when starting for open loop algorithm.

Parameters.Name: OL Idle Hold(s)
Parameters.ToolTipText: After the engine leaves cranking and enters running mode, this is the time in seconds while the duty is increased.

Parameters.Name: OL Idle Taper(s)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Open loop mode, time spent tapering the high idle duty when running in open loop.

Parameters.Name: Use Clutch SW.
Parameters.ToolTipText: When this is set to 'YES', idle won't be activated until clutch is engaged.

Parameters.Name: Clutch SW Active
Parameters.ToolTipText: Input value when switch is active.

Parameters.Name: TPS Max
Parameters.ToolTipText: The MAXIMUM throttle position before we consider us not in idle mode. Typically 3%.

Parameters.Name: RPM Min
Parameters.ToolTipText: The minimum RPM before we engage idle control. This can typically be left at 50.

Parameters.Name: RPM Max
Parameters.ToolTipText: The Maximum RPM where we engage idle control. This can typically be around 1300rpm.

Parameters.Name: Exit Idle Duty(%)
Parameters.ToolTipText: When RPM/Throttle position causes us to leave idle control, this is the duty the valve should be left running at.

Parameters.Name: PID Deadband
Parameters.ToolTipText: If the RPM error is less than this number, then the PID wont try to correct the RPM - Typically around 30 is a good setting for this.

IGBT/Passive - ECU connects the coil pin to GROUND to dwell (High Current for passive 2-wire coils)

Parameters.ToolTipText: The minimum throttle position required to activate the correction algorithm.

Parameters.Name: TPS Max
Parameters.ToolTipText: The maximum throttle percent before the algorithm is turned off - i.e. to avoid trimming the map at (rich) wide open throttle positions.

Parameters.Name: Max TPS Delta
Parameters.ToolTipText: Max TPS Delta at which the algorithm will operate.

Parameters.Name: Max MAP Delta
Parameters.ToolTipText: Max MAP Delta at which the algorithm will operate.

Parameters.Name: Step Size (%)
Parameters.ToolTipText: This is the step size in percent by which the algorithm will alter the fuelling (either increasing or decreasing) every ‘step’ until it hits the target AFR.

Parameters.Name: Eng. Rotations / Step
Parameters.ToolTipText: This is the amount of time (in engine rotations) that are allowed to pass before applying the next ‘step’.

Parameters.Name: Authority(%)
Parameters.ToolTipText: This is the maximum the algorithm will be allowed to modify the maps fuelling by to try to reach stoich. If it needs to move more than this than the map is most likely incorrect.

Parameters.Name: NB Stoich(V)
Parameters.ToolTipText: This is the voltage the control system should target for stoich fuelling - typically 0.5 volts - this can be checked with your sensors datasheet.

Parameters.Name: NB Acceptable Stoich Err.(V)
Parameters.ToolTipText: This is the allowed error in Volts at which the algorithm will consider the mixture to not need adjusting.

Parameters.Name: NB Sensor Fault(V))
Parameters.ToolTipText: This is the voltage at which a fault of the sensor will be considered, and the algorithm will not operate in this case.

Parameters.Name: Target AFR Trigger Val.
Parameters.ToolTipText: One of the more powerful aspects of the ME221 - the NARROWBAND algorithm will look at your Target AFR table and only try to trim to stoich when your target is as specified, generally, 14.7 (that is the only value a NB sensor can indicate cleanly).

Parameters.Name: WB Sens Min(V)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Under this voltage, the WBO2 sensor is considered faulty and its reading is not taken into account.

Parameters.Name: WB Sens Max(V)
Parameters.ToolTipText: Over this voltage, the WBO2 sensor is considered faulty and its reading is not taken into account.

Parameters.Name: WB Algo. P
Parameters.ToolTipText: A value (usually between 0 and 1) which dictates how much of the AFR difference is applied as a trim.

Parameters.Name: WB LTT Mode

Parameters.Name: LTT Req. Conf.
Parameters.ToolTipText: Advanced feature - confidence level required to stop calculating the long term trim for a cell.
